President Donald J. Trump has declared an emergency in the U.S. Virgin Islands due to the conditions resulting from Hurricane Irma. This declaration authorizes the Department of Homeland Security and FEMA to coordinate disaster relief efforts. The aim is to alleviate the suffering of the local population and provide assistance to save lives, protect property, and ensure public health and safety. FEMA is authorized to identify and mobilize necessary equipment and resources, with 75 percent of funding provided by the federal government. William L. Vogel has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.